Kayode Fayemi, governor of Ekiti state, will launch his book titled, ‘Unfinished Greatness: Envisioning a New Nigeria’ on Thursday (today) in Abuja. The public presentation of the book is scheduled to take place at the NAF Conference Centre at 11 am. The book presentation is to be chaired by Yakubu Gowon, former head of state. Adebayo Olukoshi, professor of Wits School of Governance and immediate past director for Africa and West Asia, International IDEA, will present the keynote address. Joe Abah, the Nigerian country director, DAI Global, is the book reviewer. The event will feature an intergenerational conversation by panellists, including Waziri Adio, former executive secretary of the Nigeria Extractive Industries Transparency Initiative(NEITI); Yemi Adamolekun, executive director, Enough-is-Enough Nigeria; Ndi Kato, executive director, Dinidari Africa, and Hamzat Bala Lawal, founder and executive director, Connected Development. TheCable will be on hand to cover the book presentation.